items.title: Iconic Brompton bike maker suffers 99% profit decline amid post-Covid bike industry turmoil
items.description: Profits fell to just £4,600 last year as the foldable bike brand fought copycat competitors and falling demand.

items.title: Why US tech ends up being controlled by European regulation
items.description: Also: Meta leadership switch, economists worry Trump will slow U.S. economy, Tesla shares slump.

items.title: What is Turo, the car-sharing app used in two deadly New Year’s Day attacks?
items.description: Turo has said that the individuals involved did not have criminal backgrounds that would have identified them as security threats.

items.title: Garbage truck stuck in a sinkhole downs power in Omaha for several hours
items.description: The sinkhole is more than 10 feet (3 meters) deep and a number of utility lines were exposed when the hole formed at an alley entrance.

items.title: Norway accelerates towards full electrification as 89% of new cars go electric
items.description: Electric vehicles surged to 89% of Norway’s new car sales last year, bringing the nation closer to its 2025 target for full electric mobility.
